article.headline: Manhattan 57, St. Peter's 49
article.story: RIVERDALE, N.Y. -- Rhamel Brown recorded his fourth double-double this season and Manhattan completed a season sweep of Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference rival Saint Peter's 57-49 Sunday. Brown notched 21 points with 10 rebounds on 8-of-10 shooting plus a 5-of-6 showing at the foul line for the Jaspers (7-15, 5-7), who entered losers of three of their past four. Just two games removed from a 63.6-percent 3-point shooting performance against Rider, Manhattan hit just 3 of 14 from 3-point range Sunday but made up for it by knocking down 30 of 36 at the foul line. Michael Alvarado led the free-throw shooting charge, making 8 of 8 for all of his points, while RaShawn Stores hit 7 of 8 en route to 10 points and Donovan Kates made 7 of 10 while scoring 10 points. Desi Washington hit four 3-pointers for the Peacocks (7-15, 2-10) en route to 16 points.
